## 5. Step-by-Step Production Deployment Guide

Follow these exact steps whenever you upload new code, change the database schema, or update dependencies.

### Step 1: Access the Server
Log into the server and switch to the API user:
```bash
ssh root@<YOUR_SERVER_IP>
su - <yourdomain>-api
```

### Step 2: Navigate to Project Directory
```bash
cd htdocs/api.<YOUR_DOMAIN>.com
```

### Step 3: Pull New Code / Upload Files
If using Git:
```bash
git pull origin main
```
*(Or upload your updated files manually using an SFTP client like FileZilla logged in as `<yourdomain>-api`)*

### Step 4: Install Dependencies
Install any newly added packages from your updated `package.json`:
```bash
npm install
```

### Step 5: Regenerate Prisma Client
Generate the type-safe Prisma client:
```bash
npx prisma generate
```

### Step 6: Deploy Database Migrations (If Schema Changed)
Apply database updates to production safely without losing data:
```bash
npx prisma migrate deploy
```

### Step 7: Build the Application
Compile TypeScript code to JavaScript (this will trigger `npx prisma generate && tsc -p tsconfig.json`):
```bash
npm run build
```

### Step 8: Restart the Server Application
Restart the running Node.js process using PM2 to apply the build updates:
```bash
pm2 restart <api-process-name>
```
